                <p>
                This project aims to develop a predictive model to identify customers more likely to engage positively with a banking campaign. By leveraging historical data, we optimize marketing strategies, improve conversion rates, and reduce unnecessary calls.
                </p>
                <p>
                The model is built using machine learning techniques, incorporating data preprocessing, feature engineering, and classification algorithms. Various evaluation metrics ensure the model's effectiveness in predicting customer engagement.
                </p>
                <p>
                Key techniques used: Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forest, and Gradient Boosting.
                </p>
